<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
This is the second record of the taxonomically difficult genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Woodson" authorityYear="1930" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Trachomitum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trachomitum" order="Gentianales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Trachomitum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Greece (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F7677543" captionText="Figure 2. Trachomitum venetum from Nomos Xanthis (photo: P. Doumas)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e81817.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/640519" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">2</figureCitation>
). The first one comes from the Island of Limnos, in the northern Aegean (
<bibRefCitation author="Yannitsaros, A." editor="Kamari, G." journalOrPublisher="G. I. Petraki, Patras" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7670213" refString="Yannitsaros, A., Economidou, E., Delipetrou, P., Bazos, I., Georgiou, K., 2001. New data on the distribution of some plant taxa in the Aegean area. In: Kamari, G., Psaras, G., Constantinidis, Th., Eds., Proceedings. G. I. Petraki, Patras" title="New data on the distribution of some plant taxa in the Aegean area" volumeTitle="Proceedings." year="2001">Yannitsaros et al. 2001</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Panitsa, M." journalOrPublisher="Willdenowia" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="79 - 105" refId="B7669051" refString="Panitsa, M., Snogerup, B., Snogerup, S., Tzanoudakis, D., 2003. Floristic investigation of Lemnos Island (NE Aegean area, Greece). Willdenowia 33: 79 - 105" title="Floristic investigation of Lemnos Island (NE Aegean area, Greece)" volume="33" year="2003">Panitsa et al. 2003</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bergmeier, E." journalOrPublisher="Flora Mediterranea" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="233 - 246" refId="B7667858" refString="Bergmeier, E., Ristow, M., Krause, J., Meyer, S., Panitsa, M., 2021. Phytodiversity of Limnos (North Aegean, Greece) - an update and evaluation. Flora Mediterranea 31: 233 - 246" title="Phytodiversity of Limnos (North Aegean, Greece) - an update and evaluation" volume="31" year="2021">Bergmeier et al. 2021</bibRefCitation>
) (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F7677547" captionText="Figure 3. Distribution map of Trachomitum venetum, Sedum confertiflorum and Saxifraga sibirica in Greece." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e81817.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/656543" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">3</figureCitation>
). Having a different opinion than that of 
<bibRefCitation author="Stearn, W. T." journalOrPublisher="Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7669356" refString="Stearn, W. T., 1978. Flora of Turkey and the East Aegean Islands Vol 6. Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh" title="Flora of Turkey and the East Aegean Islands Vol 6" year="1978">Stearn (1978)</bibRefCitation>
and the preceded authors, we attribute the plants from Nomos Xanthis and Limnos Island (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">J. Krause &amp; M. Ristow 265/19</emphasis>
, Limnos, Herb. Ristow!) to 
<taxonomicName genus="Tr." lsidName="Tr. venetum" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="species" species="venetum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Tr. venetum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authority="subsp. venetum" genus="Tr." lsidName="Tr. venetum subsp. venetum" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="subSpecies" species="venetum" subSpecies="venetum">Tr. venetum subsp. venetum</taxonomicName>
) instead of 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. sarmatiense" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="species" species="sarmatiense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">T. sarmatiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Woodson (
<taxonomicName genus="Tr." lsidName="Tr. venetum subsp. sarmatiense" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="subSpecies" species="venetum" subSpecies="sarmatiense">Tr. venetum subsp. sarmatiense</taxonomicName>
(Woodson) Avetisjan). This is in accordance with 
<bibRefCitation author="Rechinger, K. H." journalOrPublisher="Akademische Druck- u. Verlagsanstalt, Graz" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7669288" refString="Rechinger, K. H., 1974. Flora Iranica, Apocynaceae, No. 103. Akademische Druck- u. Verlagsanstalt, Graz" title="Flora Iranica, Apocynaceae, No. 103" year="1974">Rechinger (1974)</bibRefCitation>
, who treated the genus in the same way for Flora Iranica, 
<bibRefCitation author="Woodson, R. E." journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="1 - 212" refId="B7670928" refString="Woodson, R. E., 1930. Studies in the Apocynaceae. I. A critical study of the Apocynoideae (with special reference to the genus Apocynum). Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden 17: 1 - 212" title="Studies in the Apocynaceae. I. A critical study of the Apocynoideae (with special reference to the genus Apocynum)" volume="17" year="1930">Woodson (1930)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Markgraf, F." journalOrPublisher="Cambridge University Press, Cambridge" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7668897" refString="Markgraf, F., 1972. Flora Europaea Vol. 3. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge" title="Flora Europaea Vol. 3" year="1972">Markgraf (1972)</bibRefCitation>
. The Greek plants mostly have lanceolate, acute leaves, conspicuous bracts, lanceolate and acute calyx-lobes up to 2 mm and corolla-lobes 1/2 to almost as long as the corolla tube. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Α">Α</normalizedToken>
comparison of Greek plants with the type specimen of 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. sarmatiense" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="species" species="sarmatiense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">T. sarmatiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(a.n. 00093153, GH!) showed significant differences in the above-mentioned characters. The latter has ovate to ovate-lanceolate leaves with obtuse apex, inconspicuous bracts, ovate and obtuse calyx-lobes up to 1 mm and corolla-lobes shorter than 1/3 of the corolla tube. Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. sarmatiense" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="species" species="sarmatiense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">T. sarmatiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to have a more eastern distribution (
<bibRefCitation author="Woodson, R. E." journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="1 - 212" refId="B7670928" refString="Woodson, R. E., 1930. Studies in the Apocynaceae. I. A critical study of the Apocynoideae (with special reference to the genus Apocynum). Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden 17: 1 - 212" title="Studies in the Apocynaceae. I. A critical study of the Apocynoideae (with special reference to the genus Apocynum)" volume="17" year="1930">Woodson 1930</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pobedimova, E. G." journalOrPublisher="Phytologia Balcanica" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7669225" refString="Pobedimova, E. G., 1952. Flora SSSR, Vol. XVIII, Metachlamydeae." title="Flora SSSR, Vol. XVIII, Metachlamydeae" year="1952">Pobedimova 1952</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Markgraf, F." journalOrPublisher="Cambridge University Press, Cambridge" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7668897" refString="Markgraf, F., 1972. Flora Europaea Vol. 3. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge" title="Flora Europaea Vol. 3" year="1972">Markgraf 1972</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rechinger, K. H." journalOrPublisher="Akademische Druck- u. Verlagsanstalt, Graz" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7669288" refString="Rechinger, K. H., 1974. Flora Iranica, Apocynaceae, No. 103. Akademische Druck- u. Verlagsanstalt, Graz" title="Flora Iranica, Apocynaceae, No. 103" year="1974">Rechinger 1974</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Euro + Med," journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7668118" refString="Euro+Med, , 2006+ [continuously updated]." year="2006 + [continuously updated]">Euro+Med 2006+ [continuously updated]</bibRefCitation>
), whereas 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. venetum" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="species" species="venetum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">T. venetum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grows in south-east Europe and the eastern Mediterranean area, including Cyprus. As a consequence, 
<taxonomicName genus="Tr." lsidName="Tr. sarmatiense" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="species" species="sarmatiense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Tr. sarmatiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be excluded from the Greek flora.
</paragraph>
